另外一种运动 在经过研究后…

60
00:03:12,930 --> 00:03:15,190
again these are all tentative results;
我要重申 这些都是初步结果

61
00:03:15,990 --> 00:03:17,990
there've been pilot studies about it.
有人对这种运动做过初步研究

62
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:19,580
The ends,
最后结果

63
00:03:19,780 --> 00:03:22,830
the sample sizes are not large enough yet to say definitively,
因为样本不足 暂时无法下确切结论

64
00:03:23,020 --> 00:03:24,510
just like we can say about aerobic exercise,
但我们可以确切地说有氧运动

65
00:03:24,760 --> 00:03:26,270
it has similar effect
产生的效果能媲美

66
00:03:26,490 --> 00:03:29,170
to some of our most powerful psychiatric drugs.
一些强效精神病药物

67
00:03:30,150 --> 00:03:32,640
That's definitive- there are tons of studies on it
这个结论是确切的 有大量研究来支持

68
00:03:32,850 --> 00:03:35,660
ever since Babyak in 2000 as well as before.
包括Babyak2000年以来的研究 以及之前的

69
00:03:36,040 --> 00:03:38,520
But another form of exercise that has begun to be studied
另一种开始被研究的运动

70
00:03:38,720 --> 00:03:42,230
with some very promising results is interval training.
得出可喜的结果 那就是间歇运动

71
00:03:43,300 --> 00:03:47,500
Interval training would be,say,running at,
间歇运动就是 以跑步为例子

72
00:03:47,890 --> 00:03:51,450
between 90 and 95 percent of your maximum heart rate.
达到最大心率的90%到95%

73
00:03:51,690 --> 00:03:56,710
So if you are 20,your maximum heart rate would be,would be 200,
如果你20岁 你最大心率就是200

74
00:03:56,940 --> 00:03:58,780
because it's 220 minus your age.
计算公式是220减去年龄

75
00:03:59,010 --> 00:04:05,610
Then you need to be running at around at 180 to 190 pulse rate,
所以你跑步的心率要达到180到190

76
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:06,870
which is hard,which is tough,
强度非常高

77
00:04:07,060 --> 00:04:08,910
which you can't do for a very long time.
不能持续很长时间

78
00:04:09,130 --> 00:04:13,780
But doing it for as little as 30 seconds up to a minute
但如果能持续30秒到一分钟

79
00:04:14,270 --> 00:04:15,140
and then resting,
然后休息

80
00:04:15,340 --> 00:04:19,340
letting your heart rate go back down to 60 percent
让你的心率下降到最大心率的60%

81
00:04:19,590 --> 00:04:23,640
of its maximum say 120,and then doing another interval.
也就是120 然后重复这个间歇运动

82
00:04:23,840 --> 00:04:26,130
That has been shown with pilot studies only
有初步研究表明这种运动

83
00:04:26,350 --> 00:04:28,450
to have remarkable effects.
能产生显著效果

84
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:33,290
In fact,often more powerful than aerobic exercise on its own,
通常效果甚至比单纯做有氧运动更大

85
00:04:33,540 --> 00:04:36,290
and lasts for even longer- the effect.
而且持续时间更长

86
00:04:37,070 --> 00:04:38,640
So- again,
所以 再说回来

87
00:04:38,860 --> 00:04:41,260
I did not introduce it officially as part of the class,
我没有在课堂上正式介绍这种运动

88
00:04:41,460 --> 00:04:43,690
but since many of you asked,I am introducing it.
但很多同学问起 所以现在介绍一下

89
00:04:43,860 --> 00:04:45,540
Because I want to introduce you only things
因为我只想给大家介绍

90
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:49,240
that are with very robust results.
那些有确切结论的运动

91
00:04:51,310 --> 00:04:53,460
John Ratey talks about this.
John Ratey也谈过这种运动

92
00:04:53,660 --> 00:04:55,300
And I'll talk a little bit about John Ratey in a minute.
我等一下会讲John Ratey

93
00:04:55,450 --> 00:04:57,450
He's the Harvard Medical psychatrist
他是哈佛医学院的精神医生

94
00:04:57,610 --> 00:05:00,210
who is probably the leading proponent in research
可以说他是一个前沿的倡导者

95
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:02,770
in the area of exercise and mental health.
在研究运动和精神健康这个领域

96
00:05:03,130 --> 00:05:06,450
