00:32:36,590 --> 00:32:37,980
they said "let's study the best."
他们说"我们来研究最好的冥想者"

571
00:32:38,180 --> 00:32:40,770
So they contacted the Dalai Lama himself and said,
所以他们联系了达赖喇嘛 说

572
00:32:40,930 --> 00:32:42,820
"can you suggest some people who have been meditating
"你能推荐一些冥想了

573
00:32:42,960 --> 00:32:45,460
for a very long time- serious meditators;
很久的认真的冥想者吗

574
00:32:45,650 --> 00:32:48,270
and we want to study their brain."
我们想研究他们的大脑"

575
00:32:48,430 --> 00:32:50,740
So they did.And they brought them in.
他们找到了 把这些人找来

576
00:32:50,920 --> 00:32:53,080
And what they looked for,the first thing,remember,
他们研究的第一样东西是 大家应该记得

577
00:32:53,260 --> 00:32:57,110
left to right prefrontal cortex ratio.
左前额皮层和右前额皮层的比例

578
00:32:57,430 --> 00:32:59,120
And if you remember,we talked about it-
大家记得 我们之前谈过

579
00:32:59,340 --> 00:33:02,820
people who are happier generally have more activation
快乐的人通常更活跃的地方

580
00:33:03,020 --> 00:33:05,500
on the left side of the prefrontal cortex;
是左前额皮层

581
00:33:05,710 --> 00:33:08,140
people who are less happy have more activation
不快乐的人更活跃的地方

582
00:33:08,300 --> 00:33:10,680
on the right side of the prefrontal cortex.
是右前额皮层

583
00:33:10,900 --> 00:33:13,120
So that ratio is important.
所以这个比例很重要

584
00:33:13,310 --> 00:33:18,570
And it's one of the "objective" means of measuring happiness.
它是测量快乐的一个"客观"手段

585
00:33:18,780 --> 00:33:20,680
One of the things that they have found is that
他们得出的一个发现是

586
00:33:20,840 --> 00:33:22,160
there is very high correlation
两者之间存在很大关联

587
00:33:22,330 --> 00:33:25,690
between what our brains look like under the scanner
在扫描器下看到的大脑

588
00:33:25,890 --> 00:33:30,570
and our self-report about how happy we are-
和我们对自己是否快乐的自我报告

589
00:33:30,750 --> 00:33:34,660
not 100 percent correlation,not at 1,but pretty high,
当然不是100%的关联 但也不低 很高

590
00:33:35,340 --> 00:33:40,330
suggesting the self-reports are pretty,are quite reliable.
这表明自我报告是很可靠的

591
00:33:40,600 --> 00:33:44,220
But anyway,so they wanted to look at the brain of the meditators
总之 他们想研究这些冥想者的大脑

592
00:33:44,420 --> 00:33:47,580
And when they looked at the general public,
他们再比较普通大众

593
00:33:47,790 --> 00:33:50,100
we all exist on a Bell curve.
我们都在一个钟形曲线内

594
00:33:50,650 --> 00:33:53,170
The happier people are further on
快乐的人更靠前

595
00:33:53,600 --> 00:33:55,260
more activation on the left side;
左侧皮层更活跃

596
00:33:55,440 --> 00:33:56,960
the less happy people are further-
不快乐的人更靠后

597
00:33:57,180 --> 00:34:01,920
more activation,higher ratio on the right side.
右侧皮层更活跃

598
00:34:03,610 --> 00:34:05,540
And then they brought in the meditators.
然后他们找来这些冥想者

599
00:34:06,210 --> 00:34:09,650
And they measured their left to right prefrontal cortex.
测出他们左前额皮层和左前额皮层的比例

600
00:34:10,340 --> 00:34:12,200
And here is what they found.
这是他们的研究发现

601
00:34:12,730 --> 00:34:14,530
This is the normal Bell curve.
这是正常的钟形曲线

602
00:34:14,790 --> 00:34:16,700
This is where the meditators were.
冥想者在这里

603
00:34:16,880 --> 00:34:20,900
This is from 2001- since,they have found numerous meditators
这是2001年的研究 他们找了很多冥想者

604
00:34:21,110 --> 00:34:23,880
that are quite literally off the chart,
他们几乎偏离了这个图

605
00:34:24,680 --> 00:34:27,600
suggesting very high levels of well being and happiness.
表明快乐的程度很高

606
00:34:27,750 --> 00:34:29,990
Being susceptible to positive emotions,
他们很容易感染积极情绪

607
00:34:30,210 --> 00:34:33,380
and resilient in the face of painful emotions.
对痛苦情绪的抵抗力很强

608
00:34:34,970 --> 00:34:36,080
So this is a remarkable result.
这是一个很惊人的结果

609
00:34:36,190 --> 00:34:39,200
Again,results that are not seen before
这些结果之前没人发现过

610
00:34:39,410 --> 00:34:41,030
until they measured these meditators.
直到他们研究了这些冥想者

611
00:34:41,270 --> 00:34:41,860
The other things that
另一个研究方面就是

612
00:34:42,020 --> 00:34:45,370
they were interested is looking at other important indicator
他们想看看另一个重要的指标

613
00:34:45,570 --> 00:34:49,140
for well being and calmness is the startle response.
衡量健康和冷静的惊吓反应

614
00:34:49,990 --> 00:34:51,840
When you hear a bang,you startle.
当你听到一声巨响 你会吓一跳

615
00:34:53,960 --> 00:34:55,280
And the startle response is important,
这个惊吓反应很重要

616
00:34:55,430 --> 00:34:59,040
because the easier you get startled,
因为你越容易受到惊吓

617
00:34:59,260 --> 00:35:02,490
generally it's correlated to the higher levels of anxiety,
通常说明你焦虑程度更高

618
00:35:02,690 --> 00:35:05,000
susceptibility at least to anxiety.
至少容易产生焦虑

619
00:35:06,610 --> 00:35:10,110
And everyone has this startle response to some degree.
大家都有一定的惊吓反应

620
00:35:10,330 --> 00:35:13,080
Even marksmen and women in the military,
即使是军队里的神枪手

621
00:35:13,550 --> 00:35:15,320
you know,who shoot their guns everyday
他们每天都射枪

622
00:35:15,530 --> 00:35:17,860
and they are trying to remain completely focus.
他们要完全集中注意力

623
00:35:18,580 --> 00:35:21,390
Even they startle,when the gun goes off.
当枪走火时 他们也会受到惊吓

624
00:35:21,590 --> 00:35:23,690
They flinch.Very slightly,but they do.
他们会微微地抖一下 这也是惊吓反应

625
00:35:23,930 --> 00:35:27,200
So it's impossible to suppress the startle response.
要压抑惊吓反应是不可能的

626
00:35:28,270 --> 00:35:29,760
Or so they thought.
或者说当时的人是这样想的

627
00:35:31,280 --> 00:35:33,880
When Paul Ackerman brought these meditators in
Paul Ackerman找来这些冥想者

628
00:35:34,140 --> 00:35:38,440
and asked them to maintain complete equanimity and calmness,
叫他们保持绝对镇定和冷静

629
00:35:40,280 --> 00:35:41,940
and he startled them.
他吓他们

630
00:35:42,830 --> 00:35:48,710
There was no reaction whatsoever.First time in recorded history.
他们一点反应都没有 有记录以来第一次

631
00:35:48,910 --> 00:35:52,550
That people are,have been able to suppress the startle response.
有人能够抑压自己的惊吓反应

632
