Here was what Daniel Goleman writes about this in his book,
Goleman writes在他的书中这样写道

633
00:35:55,510 --> 00:35:59,960
Destructive Emotions: "Given that the larger someone's startle,
破坏性情绪 "一个人惊吓反应越大

634
00:36:00,120 --> 00:36:00,880
the more intensely that
那个人就越可能

635
00:36:01,020 --> 00:36:03,430
person tends to experience upsetting emotions,
出现消极情绪

636
00:36:03,650 --> 00:36:06,810
Oser's performance had tantalizing implications,
Oser的表现有着有趣的含意

637
00:36:07,040 --> 00:36:11,110
suggesting a remarkable level of emotional equanimity."
表明他的情绪有着惊人的镇定"

638
00:36:13,340 --> 00:36:15,750
That equanimity was also contagious-
这种镇定还会传染

639
00:36:15,940 --> 00:36:20,040
so people who tried to argue with these monks,
如果有人想和这些喇嘛争吵

640
00:36:20,240 --> 00:36:22,510
