Just like it would be counter-productive
同样会有反作用的

1166
01:12:01,220 --> 01:12:08,260
to try a meddle with the digestion that our bodies go through,
是我们想干预体内的

1167
01:12:08,420 --> 01:12:10,070
the digestive process.
消化过程时

1168
01:12:10,250 --> 01:12:12,360
It happens independent of us.
消化不受我们控制

1169
01:12:12,580 --> 01:12:16,550
If we try playing with it,open it,look at it,help it,
如果我们想左右它 看清它 分析它 促进它

1170
01:12:16,770 --> 01:12:18,380
we'll only hurt it.
我们只会伤害它

1171
01:12:18,590 --> 01:12:23,460
Why? Because the internal mind,the internal healer,
为什么?因为我们体内的主宰 体内的医生

1172
01:12:24,220 --> 01:12:28,820
the internal wisdom knows best to deal with certain things-
体内的智慧最擅长处理某些事

1173
01:12:29,040 --> 01:12:30,400
not everything,but certain things.
不是所有事 但是某一些事

1174
01:12:30,600 --> 01:12:33,400
Such as digestion.Such as very often,not always,
例如消化 还有通常的 不是所有的

1175
01:12:33,560 --> 01:12:38,410
but very often with mental afflictions,with painful emotions.
通常的精神问题 痛苦情绪

1176
01:12:39,010 --> 01:12:41,130
So we are moving,we are shifting our focus
所以我们要把注意力

1177
01:12:41,340 --> 01:12:44,750
from trying to fix to simply be with that emotion,
从解决这种情绪转移到与它同在

1178
01:12:44,940 --> 01:12:50,200
with that experience,with the manifestation of the pain.
感受这种痛苦的身体反应

1179
01:12:51,750 --> 01:12:55,060
In their book,William who teaches at Oxford:
在他们的书中 在牛津任职的William说

1180
01:12:55,260 --> 01:12:59,280
"Trying to get rid of depression in the usual problem-solving way
"想消除抑郁是通常的解决办法

1181
01:12:59,460 --> 01:13:04,210
trying to 'fix' what's 'wrong' with us,just digs us in deeper.
想解决不对劲的地方 只会让我们陷得更深

1182
01:13:04,450 --> 01:13:09,420
Rumination is part of the problem,not part of the solution."
苦苦思索是问题症结之一 不是解决方法"

1183
01:13:09,960 --> 01:13:12,120
Now the emphasis here is on rumination.
这里强调苦苦思索

1184
01:13:12,350 --> 01:13:13,440
It's not- and we've talked about it at all,
它并不等同于…我们之前谈过

1185
01:13:13,590 --> 01:13:16,360
it's not like if you write in your journal,it's not helpful.
它并不等同于写日记 它是没有益处的

1186
01:13:16,560 --> 01:13:18,400
It's good for you to write about issues
把你面对的问题写进日记里

1187
01:13:18,560 --> 01:13:20,040
that you are dealing with in your journal.
是有益于你的

1188
01:13:20,220 --> 01:13:23,090
It's good to talk to a very close friend.
和亲密朋友谈谈 是有益于你的

1189
01:13:24,100 --> 01:13:25,040
But just rumination,
但如果钻斗角尖

1190
01:13:25,230 --> 01:13:29,060
going over the same scenario over and over again.
一次又一次地思索这个问题

1191
01:13:29,580 --> 01:13:34,480
Ruminating about it,trying to fix it very often makes it worse.
苦苦思索它 想解决它 通常会使它恶化

1192
01:13:35,090 --> 01:13:37,450
And we would be better off just going to the emotion,
如果我们只是感受这股情绪

1193
01:13:37,640 --> 01:13:39,890
going to the physical manifestation.
感受身体反应 反而会更好

1194
01:13:41,060 --> 01:13:42,580
Try it.See what's right for you.
大家试试 看哪种方法适合自己

1195
01:13:42,770 --> 01:13:44,390
It may be right for you to you know,
也许适合你的方法是

1196
01:13:44,570 --> 01:13:46,080
write half an hour on one occasion
找个时间写半小时

1197
01:13:46,260 --> 01:13:49,100
and then just meditate on it for 10 minutes.
然后冥想10分钟

1198
01:13:49,340 --> 01:13:51,900
Or it may be right for you to only write about it.
也许光是写更适合你

1199
01:13:52,550 --> 01:13:53,590
It's different for different people.
每个人的方法都不同

1200
01:13:53,790 --> 01:13:54,260
But what I'm doing here
我给大家讲这些

1201
01:13:54,440 --> 01:13:58,300
is I'm adding another tool to your psychological tool box.
只是希望教会大家另一个心理工具

1202
01:13:59,050 --> 01:14:01,780
And just like we can cognitively reconstruct,
例如我们可以借助认知重建

1203
01:14:02,170 --> 01:14:05,090
as opposed to seeing it as a threat,to see it as a challenge;
把威胁看成挑战

1204
01:14:05,280 --> 01:14:09,780
as opposed to seeing it as a threat,to see it as a privilege;
把威胁看成荣幸

1205
01:14:10,610 --> 01:14:11,850
as opposed to seeing it as a failure,
把失败

1206
01:14:12,050 --> 01:14:14,880
just to see it as a learning opportunity.
看成一次学习机会

1207
01:14:15,240 --> 01:14:19,410
We can also have emotional reconstruction,
我们也能情绪重建

1208
01:14:20,460 --> 01:14:23,320
where instead of just thinking and ruminating about it,
不要对情绪苦苦思索

1209
01:14:23,540 --> 01:14:25,410
we go to the experience.
而是去感受它

1210
01:14:30,610 --> 01:14:33,720
"With the shift trying to ignore or eliminate physical discomfort
"不再尝试无视和消除身体不适

1211
01:14:33,860 --> 01:14:36,260
to paying attention with friendly curiosity,
而是抱着关怀之心去关注它

1212
01:14:36,450 --> 01:14:42,230
we can transform- quite literally transform our experience."
我们就能真真正正地改变我们的感受"

1213
01:14:44,550 --> 01:14:46,450
I'm going to leave you today with a last tip.
今天我教大家最后一个方法

1214
01:14:46,610 --> 01:14:48,630
And this is something that is very important
这个方法很重要

1215
01:14:48,820 --> 01:14:53,000
and that I highly recommend doing- for all of you,no exception.
我非常推荐 你们所有人都要学 没有例外

1216
01:14:54,040 --> 01:14:58,420
What I highly recommend doing is breathing.
我非常推荐的方法是呼吸

1217
01:14:58,990 --> 01:15:02,140
It's very,very important to breathe.
呼吸很重要

1218
01:15:03,050 --> 01:15:07,750
And in fact,it's the one thing
事实上 它是唯一

1219
01:15:07,900 --> 01:15:10,980
that's common to all the mindful meditation practices
所有正念冥想的共通点

1220
01:15:11,130 --> 01:15:13,450
and something that you can introduce to your life-
你可以把它应用于生活中

1221
01:15:13,840 --> 01:15:15,680
of course I mean proper breathing.
当然我所说的呼吸是正确呼吸

1222
01:15:15,890 --> 01:15:17,810
Something that you can introduce to your life,
你可以应用到你的生活中

1223
01:15:18,010 --> 01:15:22,760
even if you don't meditate for 15 minutes or 45 minutes a day.
即使你没有一天冥想15分钟 或45分钟

1224
01:15:25,020 --> 01:15:26,990
What I'm talking about here is deep breathing.
我所说的呼吸是深呼吸

1225
01:15:27,200 --> 01:15:28,600
Because here is what happens:
因为现实情况是

1226
01:15:28,860 --> 01:15:32,740
in our modern world,we are mostly stressed and anxious.
在现代世界 我们经常感到紧张焦虑

1227
01:15:32,940 --> 01:15:36,440
As a result of this,our breathing becomes shallow.
因此我们的呼吸变得很浅

1228
01:15:36,940 --> 01:15:38,500
And as a result of shallow breathing,
因为呼吸很浅

1229
01:15:38,690 --> 01:15:39,370
when our breathing is shallow,
当我们呼吸浅时

1230
01:15:39,580 --> 01:15:41,920
we become even more stressed and anxious.
我们就变得更紧张焦虑

1231
01:15:42,140 --> 01:15:43,860
And we go into this vicious cycle,
我们就会陷入一个恶性循环

1232
01:15:44,050 --> 01:15:50,110
vicious downward spiral of the "fight or flight" response.
一个"或战或逃反应"的恶性循环

1233
01:15:50,910 --> 01:15:53,360
And that's how we go through most of our days.
我们平常就是这样处理的

1234
01:15:54,360 --> 01:15:56,060
Fortunately we can reverse this.
庆幸的是我们可以扭转这种循环

1235
01:15:56,310 --> 01:15:58,290
And we can reverse this very quickly.
我们可以马上扭转它

1236
01:15:58,490 --> 01:15:59,370
Because we also know that
因为我们还知道

1237
01:15:59,520 --> 01:16:02,630
calm and well being leads to deep breathing;
平静和健康促进我们深呼吸

1238
01:16:02,830 --> 01:16:06,490
and deep breathing in turn leads to calm and well being.
深呼吸又能反过来促进平静和健康

1239
01:16:07,300 --> 01:16:09,820
We can reverse the "fight or flight" response
我们可以扭转这种"或战或逃"的反应

1240
01:16:10,010 --> 01:16:12,160
and enter what Herbert Benson calls,
进入Herbert Benson所说的

1241
01:16:12,340 --> 01:16:18,800
the relaxation response within as little as three deep breaths.
放松反应 只需三个深呼吸的时间

1242
01:16:20,910 --> 01:16:22,910
We can introduce these three deep breaths
我们可以把这三个深呼吸的方法

1243
01:16:23,080 --> 01:16:24,780
strategically throughout the day.
有计划地应用在一天的生活中

1244
01:16:24,990 --> 01:16:28,050
Just before class starts; just when the class ends;
上课前 下课后

1245
01:16:28,250 --> 01:16:30,510
just when I wake up in the morning;
早上醒来时

1246
01:16:30,700 --> 01:16:33,170
or the last thing before I go to bed.
或者上床睡觉前

1247
01:16:34,610 --> 01:16:35,790
Three deep breaths,
三个深呼吸

1248
01:16:35,990 --> 01:16:39,880
strategic points through the day can transform a life.
有计划地按排到一天的时间点上 能改变你的人生

1249
01:16:43,760 --> 01:16:46,700
Andrew Weil,graduate of our medical school,
Andrew Weil 我们医学院的毕业生

1250
01:16:46,890 --> 01:16:51,000
now at the University of Arizona,in his wonderful CD,
现在任职于亚利桑那州大学 在他很棒的CD中

1251
01:16:51,190 --> 01:16:52,980
talks about breathing:
他这样说呼吸

1252
01:16:53,190 --> 01:16:56,450
"If I had to limit my advice on healthier living to just one tip,
"如果我只能说一条健康生活的建议

1253
01:16:56,680 --> 01:16:59,700
it would be simply to learn how to breathe correctly."
答案很简单 学习正确呼吸"

1254
01:16:59,900 --> 01:17:03,050
And that means breathing like a baby breathes.
这意味着 像婴儿一样呼吸

1255
01:17:03,250 --> 01:17:04,210
Into the stomach.
吸进腹部

1256
01:17:04,400 --> 01:17:07,220
I told you,I'm not going to teach you much new in this course.
我说过 这节课不会教什么新知识了

1257
01:17:07,440 --> 01:17:08,170
You know how to breathe.
你们都知道怎么呼吸

1258
01:17:08,340 --> 01:17:11,370
You learn how to breathe when you were born.
你们一出生就知道怎么呼吸

1259
01:17:12,070 --> 01:17:15,240
All we are doing now is chipping away the excess stone
现在我们要做的只是去掉多余的牵绊

1260
01:17:15,460 --> 01:17:19,680
so that you go back to your natural wisdom,your natural healer.
求助于你的自然智慧 自然医生

1261
01:17:20,360 --> 01:17:22,050
In a wonderful book,
在一本很棒的书里

1262
01:17:22,890 --> 01:17:26,920
Alia Crum's Dad- she did the article with Ellen Langer-
Alia Crum的父亲 她和Ellen Langer写了这篇文章

1263
01:17:27,170 --> 01:17:29,990
Thomas Crum gives some good advice about
她父亲Thomas Crum提了几个很好的建议

1264
01:17:30,150 --> 01:17:32,810
how we can reverse the "flight or fight" response.
如何扭转"或逃或战"反应

1265
01:17:33,000 --> 01:17:34,250
And one of the things that he advises-
他的其中一个建议

1266
01:17:34,450 --> 01:17:37,040
he says that each time you get to a red light,
就是每次遇到红灯

1267
01:17:37,270 --> 01:17:39,620
use it as an opportunity to breathe deeply-
把它当作一个深呼吸的机会

1268
01:17:39,820 --> 01:17:42,180
whether when you are walking and you get to a red light,
不管是走路 还是遇到红灯

1269
01:17:42,380 --> 01:17:43,850
or in the car.
或者在车里

1270
01:17:43,870 --> 01:17:45,670
Now in the past...I introduced it.
以前…我用过这种方法

1271
01:17:45,850 --> 01:17:48,660
In the past,every time I got to a red light,it was annoying,
以前每次遇到红灯时 都很烦躁

1272
01:17:48,890 --> 01:17:52,060
especially if the light had just changed from green.
尤其是刚刚从绿灯转成红灯时

1273
01:17:52,390 --> 01:17:55,060
Now whenever I get to a red light,
现在每次遇到红灯

1274
01:17:55,280 --> 01:17:58,600
it's an opportunity and I breathe deeply.
我都把它当作一个机会 深深呼吸

1275
01:17:58,830 --> 01:18:01,220
Introduce deep breathing to your life.
在生活中学会深呼吸

1276
01:18:01,410 --> 01:18:02,990
Just a few times a day.
一天几次

1277
01:18:03,590 --> 01:18:06,870
And that can have far-reaching consequences.
能产生深远影响

1278
01:18:07,320 --> 01:18:09,750
So I'll see you next week.
我们下周见

1279
01:18:09,990 --> 01:18:11,510
And until then,breathe.
在此之前 大家深呼吸

1280
01:18:11,730 --> 01:18:16,590
